                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d425">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/929: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-01-31T15:00:00-02:00"
                            >January 31, 1933—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 31—1:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>10. Department’s telegram No. 18, January 30, 5 p.m. Have conversed with Minister
                    for Foreign Affairs over your telegram. He will adopt your suggestions should
                    circumstances develop to the point you outline. Up to noon today no report from
                    Lima to Brazil’s request for acceptance without modification of her
                    proposal.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morgan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
